<p>I want to load a config.xml file in c# an split it in 4 different lists.  The XML file looks like this:</p>  <pre><code>    &lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?&gt;     &lt;Configs version="1.0" author="AP"&gt;         &lt;config ver="9.7"&gt;             &lt;start&gt;00090[ABCDEF].*&lt;/start&gt;             &lt;lines&gt;544&lt;/lines&gt;             &lt;configFile&gt;cfg_9_7.xml&lt;/configFile&gt;         &lt;/config&gt;         &lt;config ver="9.7_512"&gt;             &lt;start&gt;00090[1-9].*&lt;/start&gt;             &lt;lines&gt;512&lt;/lines&gt;             &lt;configFile&gt;cfg_9_7_v2_512.xml&lt;/configFile&gt;         &lt;/config&gt;         &lt;config ver="9.7"&gt;             &lt;start&gt;00090[2-7].*&lt;/start&gt;             &lt;lines&gt;256&lt;/lines&gt;             &lt;configFile&gt;cfg_9_7_small.xml&lt;/configFile&gt;         &lt;/config&gt;     &lt;/Configs&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I need to split the version of a config (<code>config ver="..."</code>), the start, lines and <code>configFile</code>. All of the Lists can save Strings so i only need the values and the attribute. I want to make this with a Linq to XML because i think its a lot faster and smaller than my "Read all Lines and search for keywords" function:</p>  <pre><code>    var cfg = File.ReadAllLines(folder + keyCfg);     List&lt;String&gt; config = new List&lt;String&gt;(cfg);     Boolean keyFormatConfig = false;     for (int i = 0; i &lt; config.Count; i++)     {         String line = config[i];         while (line.StartsWith(" ") || line.StartsWith("\t"))         {             line = line.Substring(1);         }         if (line.StartsWith("&lt;config ver=\""))         {             keyFormatConfig = true;         }         if (line.StartsWith("&lt;/config&gt;"))         {             keyFormatConfig = false;         }         if (keyFormatConfig)         {             if (line.StartsWith("&lt;config ver=\""))             {                 String[] name = line.Split('"');                 if (name.Length &gt;= 2)                 {                     Version.Add(name[1]);                 }             }             else if (line.StartsWith("&lt;start&gt;"))             {                 line = line.Substring(7);                 if (line.Contains("&lt;"))                 {                     String[] value = line.Split('&lt;');                     Start.Add(value[0]);                 }             }             else if (line.StartsWith("&lt;lines&gt;"))             {                 line = line.Substring(7);                 if (line.Contains("&lt;"))                 {                     String[] value = line.Split('&lt;');                     Lines.Add(value[0]);                 }             }             else if (line.StartsWith("&lt;configFile&gt;"))             {                 line = line.Substring(12);                 if (line.Contains("&lt;"))                 {                     String[] value = line.Split('&lt;');                     ConfigFile.Add(value[0]);                 }             }         }     } </code></pre>  <p>Sorry for my bad English :)</p>